  "text": "Sp17. The CD8 T cell responses to Sp17(1) and Sp17 [CITATION_1] were investigated in samples from two HLA-A * 0201-positive patients (1 and 2), who were both in remission one year after initial diagnosis. A significant -IFN response to both Sp17 peptides was still detectable in the two patients after one year (Figure 1(a) ) suggesting the persistence of a pool of circulating memory CD8-positive T cells to the Sp17 protein.",
